article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 66, SE Louisiana 49
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Matt Kingsley scored 21 points and grabbed a team-high 11 rebounds to help lead Stephen F. Austin to a 66-49 win against Southeastern Louisiana on Saturday night. Josh Alexander added 14 points and nine rebounds for the Lumberjacks (9-5). He also had three 3-pointers. The Lions (8-7) held the game close in the first half, trailing 33-31 at the break. But Stephen F. Austin rallied in the second half and went ahead for good with 17:50 remaining. Daryl Cohen led Southeastern Louisiana with 12 points, including a pair of 3-pointers. Terry Bryant added 10 points, and Joseph Polite grabbed a team-high six rebounds. The Lions hit only 24 percent of their second-half shots.
